Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) - The paper focuses on improving the reconstruction quality of video and hyperspectral images, which are important topics in computer vision. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper involves compressive sensing, which is a key concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with video and hyperspectral images, which are important types of multimedia data. 
4. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper proposes a joint model and an alternating minimization algorithm, which are common techniques in machine learning. 
5. cs.SP (Signal Processing) - The paper involves processing of signals (video and hyperspectral images) and proposes a method to improve the reconstruction quality.
